if the mass point moves along the geodesic line in the original
reference system , it will not move along the geodesic
line in the new coordinate system .
It means that, in an arbitrary curved space-time and in an arbitrary
coordinate system, a mass point will not move along the geodesic line,
or in most general case, the geodesic line is not the trajectory
of a free mass point.  


